This paper is about improving the performance of information retrieval systems through query expansion. The methods tested and compared in the paper are based on cooccurrence measures and probability distribution of terms, which are commonly used in information retrieval and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). However, the paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques, such as naive combination of methods, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DL (Deep Learning).
